      "The General Entertainment Authority (GEA) was established in 2016 as part of Vision 2030 to regulate and grow Saudi Arabia's entertainment sector. Since its founding, the GEA has rapidly expanded the Kingdom's entertainment landscape — but with growth comes regulation. Any event featuring live performance, public entertainment, or amplified music in a public or semi-public setting requires GEA approval.",
